{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 180°C.","Place Parmesan cheese into mixing bowl and grate <b>10 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma dish into position. Weigh lamb into Varoma dish then rub lamb with 2 teaspoons of the dried oregano and 20 g of the olive oil. Season lamb to preference with salt and pepper, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Set Varoma aside. Rinse and dry mixing bowl.","Place cooked lamb into mixing bowl and chop <b>Turbo\/1 sec\/1-2 times<b> or until a mince consistency is achieved. Transfer into a thermal serving bowl or other large bowl and cover to keep warm.","Place garlic, carrot, celery, spring onions\/shallots, remaining oregano and 30 g of the olive oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and cook <b>3 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<b>.","Add reserved lamb mince, stock paste, tomato purée and Worcestershire sauce and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/\/speed <b>. Transfer into an ovenproof dish (approx. 15 x 22 cm) and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Place butter beans and remaining 30 g olive oil into mixing bowl and blend <b>15 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, season to taste with salt and pepper and repeat blending until a smooth consistency is achieved.","Spread butter bean mash over the top of the lamb mixture and sprinkle with reserved Parmesan. Bake for 10-15 minutes (180°C) or until top is golden brown and bubbling. Serve hot."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["40 g Parmesan cheese, crust removed and cut into cubes (3 cm)","600 g water","250 g lamb meat, cut into cubes","4 tsp dried oregano","80 g olive oil","1 pinch sea salt, to taste","1 pinch ground black pepper, to taste","2 garlic cloves","2 carrots, cut into pieces","2 celery stalks, trimmed and cut into pieces","4 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into pieces","2 tsp vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","60 g tomato purée","20 g Worcestershire sauce","800 g canned butter beans, (2 cans), rinsed and drained"]}],"id":"r71929","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-YYj3PneQ3Zc\/XZQva5V7qZI\/AAAAAAAAccM\/QHvneOzRowoGo0MCoMv5NLxVzNZlCz0OgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_FlbfGvWD_OPDKfxT.png","title":"Shepherd's pie with butter bean mash","publishedAt":"2015-05-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"47.2 g","fat":"54.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20.5 g","calories":"3282 kJ \/ 781 kcal"},"usefulItems":"thermal serving bowl or other large bowl, ovenproof dish (15 x 22 cm), oven","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook<\/em> or the <em>Everyday Cookbook<\/em> for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","If cooking for one, transfer any leftovers into a freezable container and place into the freezer to enjoy later in the week.","Butter beans, also known as lima beans, have a rich buttery texture - making them the perfect substitute for mashed potato in this traditional dish. High in fibre and protein, butter beans also help to stabilise blood sugar levels after eating."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","2 portions"]}